The National Examinations Council (NECO) has advised the Borno state government to make the conduct of its examinations compulsory for all public schools so as to meet its quota for admission into the federal unity colleges. The advise came when the Registrar/Chief Executive of NECO, Prof Dantani Wushishi paid a visit to Maiduguri on Tuesday to interface with the state government. According to Wushishi,”it may interest you to know that Borno State does not fill it’s quota for admission into Federal Unity Colleges nationwide, to meet up the state quota, it is required that all public primary schools should write the National Common Entrance Examination”. JUST IN: Veteran Yoruba Actor, Tafa Oloyede Dies Ibada-Amukpe Community Elects New Executive Officers Meanwhile, Borno state has promised to render all necessary support and assistance to the National Examinations Council (NECO) to enable her deliver on its mandate.The Borno State Governor, Prof. Babagana Zulum made the pledge through a representative, his Chief of Staff, Alhaji Usman Jidda Shuwa Zulum said in view of the important role NECO plays in the educational development of the nation, the state government will continue to accord the Council the necessary support and assistance. While commendeding NECO for conducting credible and reliable Examinations over the years, the Governor enjoined the Council to embark on more sensitization and enlightenment campaigns to educate the public on the activities and mandate of the Council. Earlier, the Registrar, Prof. Wushishi had assured the Governor of the Council’s readiness to partner with the State Government to enhance the educational development of the State. Wushishi also lauded the state government for the prompt payment of SSCE( Internal) Registration fees of candidates from the State since the inception of the present administration in 2019.